prcStep.stepDesc: Using the 2005 Irrigated Lands data as base, parcel boundaries were adjusted where needed using 2011 NAIP imagery. Additional fields were added from the 1993 and 2000 datasets and adjusted after reviewing ground truth data and satellite imagery for irrigated parcels.

Crop Type: Crop types were determined by using a supervised classification method. Ground truth data from water commissioners, along with NASS classification data was used to provide enough training signatures for each major crop. After running the classification, zonal statistics were run to determine the majority crop type in each parcel. Parcels with two major crops were reviewed for possible field splits and divided accordingly.

This data was checked for topology errors, and final crop types were assigned from the classification work. In cases where crop type had been provided by the commissioners, that crop was treated the same as a ground truth parcel and assigned if it conflicted with the classified crop. Irrigated parcels were checked again in a QAQC procedure to ensure they comply with CDSS standards. This included checking all attributes including: all SW_COV attributes total 100, SW_WDID attributes are not duplicated, all SW_WDID attributes exist in the structure table of HydroBase. Edits and adjustments were made accordingly. All parcels comply with CDSS standards.

prcStep.stepDesc: Additional updates were made to the 2010 dataset in 2014 as a result of investigations into diversions on major structures. Through discussions with water commissioners, changes were made to structure assignments and field boundaries. Additional lands were added where needed, and some lands were removed. Surface water COV fields were also removed from the dataset. Percentages associated with multiple structures on a parcel will be handled by the models and detailed in coding in HydroBase.
